docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S4_T2.1_review.1.stdout.log:11:- `waveplan-cli` adds `--review-schedule` to `next`/`step`/`run`/`journal` argparse but immediately discards the resolved value: `_ = _resolve_review_schedule_path(...)` at lines 902, 927, 960, 981. The path is **never appended** to `tool_args` for the Go subprocess.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S4_T2.1_review.1.stdout.log:16:Spec `docs/specs/2026-05-14-swim-review-schedule-sidecar.md` Fail-Fast Rules require failure when *"the sidecar contains rows whose preconditions conflict with the base/overlay merged state"*. `ValidateReviewScheduleSidecar` only checks per-row `requires`/`produces` against `statusByAction`; it never walks the merged execution to verify the row's `requires` matches the predecessor's `produces`. A `fix` row anchored after `implement` (status `taken`) requires `review_taken` and would silently merge. Runtime would block at apply time, not at load time. If T2.2 owns this rule explicitly, fine — otherwise it belongs in T2.1's loader.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S4_T2.1_review.1.stdout.log:19:`tests/swim/test_t4_2_cli_wired.sh` exports `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW` and writes an empty‑insertions sidecar but never asserts that any subcommand returns a merged frame. `tests/swim/test_t4_1_cli_scaffold.sh` only asserts `--review-schedule` appears in `--help` and tests negative resolution. Neither test catches the dead pass-through.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S4_T2.1_review.1.stdout.log:33:### MINOR — `contextsize` and `waveplan-ps/waveplan-ps` (built binaries) appear in working tree
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S4_T2.1_review.1.stdout.log:38:1. **Wire `--review-schedule` end-to-end.** Add `flag.String("review-schedule", "", ...)` to `cmd/swim-next-resolve/main.go`, `cmd/swim-step/main.go`, `cmd/swim-run/main.go` (and `cmd/swim-journal` if relevant), pass into `swim.NextOptions.ReviewSchedulePath` / `swim.RunOptions.ReviewSchedulePath` / `swim.ApplyOptions.ReviewSchedulePath`. In `waveplan-cli`, replace `_ = _resolve_review_schedule_path(...)` with capture and append `--review-schedule <resolved>` to each `tool_args` list. Without this T2.1 has no observable effect.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S4_T2.1_review.1.stdout.log:40:2. **Add an end-to-end merge assertion.** Extend `tests/swim/test_t4_2_cli_wired.sh` (or a new bash test) to write a non-empty sidecar, run `waveplan-cli swim run --dry-run --schedule … --review-schedule …`, and `jq -e` that the report's step_ids include sidecar rows in the spec-defined merged order.
