docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S3_T1.3_implement.2.stderr.log:3243:docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S1_T1.1_review.1.stdout.log:8:`internal/swim/contracts.go:107` declares `BaseSchedulePath`, schema requires it (`docs/specs/swim-review-schedule-schema-v1.json:7`), spec mandates "explicit only" sidecar location (`docs/specs/2026-05-14-swim-review-schedule-sidecar.md:18`), yet `ValidateReviewScheduleSidecar` (contracts.go:238) accepts the `base *Schedule` and never cross-checks the field. Sidecar pointing at a different base file is silently accepted. Either (a) compare `sidecar.BaseSchedulePath` to a base-path arg, or (b) add an explicit test-locked comment that path checking lives at the CLI loader (T1.2/T2.1). Today it is neither.
