docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S3_T1.3_implement.2.stderr.log:3416:    16	`_resolve_review_schedule_path` never stats the resolved path. T1.3 ("Verify fail-fast behavior for missing or invalid review-schedule paths") will likely flunk against this impl. Add a `must_exist=True` check that emits `{ok:false, error:"review schedule path not readable: <path>", subcommand:...}` exit 2 when `Path(resolved).is_file()` is false.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S3_T1.3_implement.2.stderr.log:3418:    18	**C2. Schema file is untracked** — `docs/specs/swim-review-schedule-schema-v1.json`
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S3_T1.3_implement.2.stderr.log:3425:    25	- `waveplan-ps/waveplan-ps`: binary changed, no source diff. Looks like a local rebuild.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S3_T1.3_implement.2.stderr.log:3432:    32	Every call site is `_ = _resolve_review_schedule_path(...)`. Acceptable for T1.2 scope (T3.2 is "thread review-schedule through swim execution"), but at minimum capture the result into a named local (`review_schedule_path`) and either pass it as `--review-schedule` to the Go subprocess or add a `# T3.2: thread this` placeholder. As written, a follow-up developer has to rewire four call sites and re-test.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S3_T1.3_implement.2.stderr.log:3435:    35	Only the path-equality case is asserted. The "missing review schedule" branch (the more common operator failure) is unverified. Since the test suite for T1.2 lives here, add a case that unsets `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW`, omits `--review-schedule`, and asserts the deterministic error JSON + nonzero exit.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S3_T1.3_implement.2.stderr.log:3438:    38	Works as a green-bar workaround, but the stub schema instance won't validate once schema enforcement turns on downstream. Either (a) point it at a fixture that satisfies the actual schema, or (b) keep T4.2's pre-T1.2 behavior unaffected by gating review-schedule only in commands that need it.
